$ PowerShell: the automatic variable $psCmdlet

The → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic[automatic] variable `$psCmdLet` object represents the → Windows/PowerShell/language/cmdlet[cmdlet]
or → Windows/PowerShell/language/function[function] (with the → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Management/Automation/CmdletBindingAttribute[`cmdletBinding`] attribute) that is being executed.

The following example tries to demonstrate that `$psCmdLet` is assigned a value in a function if the function is defined with the `cmdletBinding` attribute.
